  <body>
    <div id="bg"></div>

    <section id="landing">
      <br /><br />
      <h1><br /><br /><br /><strong>Mero Yatra</strong></h1>
      <p>
        <br /><br />
        <strong
          >Our Culture Your Selection. Start Your Travel Planning Today! Find
          exciting locations and Cuisine. Highlights: Flexible Options Filter
          Available, Providing Low Fare Tips, Experience our culture.</strong
        >
      </p>
      <button type="button" name="button" onclick="enterSite();">
        Explore
      </button>
    </section>

    <div id="dimmed-bg"></div>

    <section id="full-site">
      <section id="above-fold">
        <nav>
          <ul>
            <li><a href="/">Tourify</a></li>
            <li><a href="/aboutus">Blogs</a></li>
            <!-- <li><a href="#">Deal of the week</a></li> -->
            <li><a href="/destination">Destination</a></li>
            <li><a href="/contact">Contact Us</a></li>
          </ul>
        </nav>
        <article>
          <h1>Book your next vacation with us!</h1>
          <p>
            The ideal hotel at the ideal price! Compare Prices from over 1M
            Hotels. No more headache! Compare 200+ booking sites worldwide. Save
            time with one click. Book from your Phone. No additional fees.
            Download free mobile app. Fast and Simple. 1M+ Hotels
            Worldwide.Compare Prices & Save Money on Tourify (Nepal's Largest
            Travel Website). Hidden Gems. Best Places to Eat. Tours, Attractions
            + More. Fun Things to Do. Vacation Rentals.
          </p>
          <button type="button" name="button">
            <a href="/register"> Get Started</a>
          </button>
        </article>
      </section>

      <section id="info-section">
        <article>
          <figure></figure>
          <div>
            <h2>Drira Gompa,Karnali Province</h2>
            <p>
              Gangs Rin-po-che, meaning "precious jewel of snows". at Drira
              GompaSunset Drira Gompa and Mount Kailash (Gang Rinpoche) 6638m in
              between runs the river Lha chu. It was devastated by a volcanic
              eruption in the 16th century BC, forever shaping its rugged
              landscape
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>
        <article>
          <figure></figure>
          <div>
            <h2>Nenyul Village,Mustang District</h2>
            <p>
              Nenyul village lies at the height of 3880 meters from the sea
              level. It is about 45 minutes from Lo-Manthang. When you hike to
              Kunchokling or Samjong you you will pass this village.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>
        <article>
          <figure></figure>
          <div>
            <h2>Tsum valley</h2>
            <p>
              The Tsum Valley is one of the most secluded valleys in Nepal.
              Situated in the Manaslu region, high up near the Tibetan border,
              the whole area has a definite Tibetan Buddhist feel to it and is
              quite different from the surrounding countryside. For trekkers who
              are fascinated by Tibetan culture as well as mountains,
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>
      </section>

      <section id="current-users">
        <header>
          <h4>Total Vacations Booked This Month</h4>
          <!-- <h3 id="total-users"> -->
          <h3>106,011</h3>
        </header>
      </section>
      <!-- donot remove this section  -->
      <section id="locations"></section>

      <section id="testimonials">
        <div id="testimonials-bg"></div>

        <article>
          <header>
            <h2>Our Satisfied Users</h2>
            <h5>
              Rated <span>9.6/10</span><br />
              By our verified users
            </h5>
          </header>

          <section id="reviews">
            <div class="review">
              <div class="reviewer-details">
                <figure></figure>
                <div class="details">
                  <div class="name">Keanu Reeves</div>
                  <div class="from">Works as John Wick</div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <p class="review-text">
                Greg Anderson, CPA. EVP, Chief Financial Officer at Allegiant
                Travel Company. I am near the end of my trip in Nepal. I know
                many Nepali in Australia (my home country) and they are just the
                best people. While travelling I’ve seen this time and time
                again: big smiles, generosity and humility.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="review">
              <div class="reviewer-details">
                <figure></figure>
                <div class="details">
                  <div class="name">Scarlett johansson</div>
                  <div class="from">CEO at Black Widow</div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <p class="review-text">
                Scarlett johansson.I decided to end my trip in Lumbini, I want
                to say that it was a big mistake. I have had men calling out to
                me, following me, sneakily taking my photo as I walk past,
                staring at me. It has honestly ruined my time visiting Buddha’s
                birth place.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="review">
              <div class="reviewer-details">
                <figure></figure>
                <div class="details">
                  <div class="name">Tom Holland</div>
                  <div class="from">I'm Spiderman!</div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <p class="review-text">
                The travel business has been turned upside down since the global
                pandemic began earlier this year. And while we don’t know when
                we’ll be able to move on from this, we do know that we can’t do
                it without the tour guides when we go on a vacation.
              </p>
            </div>
          </section>
          <a href="#">Leave a review</a>
          <a href="#">See all customer reviews</a>
        </article>
      </section>

      <%- include('./partials/footer.ejs') %>
    </section>

    <script
